content.review:
This paper addressed an essential task for large-scale application of object detection -- semi-supervised learning. It introduced a simple but effective Unbiased Teacher to solve the traditionally problematic data imbalance issue. 

Pros

(1) Provides strong evidences and analysis on the class-imbalance problem inherited in pseudo-labeling methods;
(2) Proposed 
      (a) an interesting learning paradigm where the teacher is the temporal ensemble of student networks;
      (b) focal loss in place of cross entropy;
(3) The experiment and ablation suggested that the resulting teacher model is not prone to class-imbalance-induced overfitting and the improvement from SOTA is significant.

Cons

Curious to know why there is a drop in AP_50 comparing to STAC.

